The paper deals with anonymizing facial attributes using machine learning algorithms, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and privacy (cs.CR) sub-categories. The proposed algorithm uses adversarial perturbations, which is a popular technique in deep learning and falls under machine learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. The paper also involves decision-making based on user's choice, which can be categorized under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category.
